---
By: Ramana Maharshi
Source:
  ID: 57c5499b-c3b2-4b09-92a9-a6e977a32050
  Locus:
    Page: 372
    Verse: 21
Tags:
  - Power
---
A man is possessed of limited powers and is miserable; he wants to expand
his powers so that he may be happy. But consider if it will be so; if with
limited perceptions one is miserable, with extended perceptions the misery
must increase proportionally.
